r.com%2Fjack-dorsey-block-ai-managers-player-coaches-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplayer-coaches%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20who%20build%20alongside%20their%20teams%2C%20while%20%26quot%3Bindividual%20contributors%26quot%3B%20use%20AI%20tools%20to%20inform%20their%20own%20decisions%20instead%20of%20waiting%20to%20be%20told%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20have%20long%20reorganized%20around%20disruptive%20technologies%2C%20from%20the%20internet%20to%20mobile%20computing.%20For%20some%2C%20AI%20is%20the%20latest%20catalyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemoving%20dedicated%20middle%20managers%20and%20offloading%20part%20of%20their%20work%20to%20AI%20is%20unconventional%20%E2%80%94%20and%20reminiscent%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftony-hsieh-explains-how-zappos-rebounded-from-employee-exodus-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZappos'%20holacracy%20experiment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%202010s.%20Block%20CEO%20Jack%20Dorsey%20has%20expressed%20an%20eventual%20desire%20to%20eliminate%20all%20managerial%20layers.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYet%2C%20for%20now%2C%20Meta%20and%20Block's%20rebranding%20may%20be%20less%20dramatic%2C%20as%20some%20of%20the%20new%20descriptions%20still%20reference%20human%20oversight%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20when%20companies%20rethink%20jobs%2C%20there%20isn't%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%20structural%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Kaufman%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20giant%20StockX%20and%20a%20leadership%20consultant.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20like%20moving%20the%20peas%20to%20the%20corn%20compartment%20in%20a%20TV%20dinner%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273ce68c6-3858-4eaf-8cbd-334f1f1015ba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20layers%20at%20all%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reorgs%20happening%20at%20Meta%20and%20Block%20are%20an%20extension%20of%20a%20years-long%20trend%20of%20companies%20trimming%20their%20managerial%20ranks%20in%20the%20name%20of%20speed%20and%20efficiency.%20Employers%20advertised%2012.3%25%20fewer%20middle-manager%20jobs%20in%202025%20than%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20job%20site%20Indeed.%20(Listings%20overall%20also%20declined.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20CEO%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20an%20earnings%20call%20in%20January%20that%20the%20company%20was%20investing%20in%20more%20AI-native%20tools%20to%20help%20flatten%20its%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20starting%20to%20see%20projects%20that%20used%20to%20require%20big%20teams%20now%20be%20accomplished%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-says-ai-letting-one-employee-do-work-of-teams-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle%20very%20talented%20person%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20a%20key%20driver.%20In%20its%20Reality%20Labs%20unit%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Meta's%20org%20leads%20handle%20reviews%20and%20promotions%20with%20support%20from%20AI%20systems%2C%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlock's%20Dorsey%20and%20Sequoia%20partner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsequoia-roelof-botha-venture-capital-return-free-risk-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoelof%20Botha%3C%2Fa%3E%20laid%20out%20their%20vision%20for%20a%20fully%20flat%20future%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20published%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20need%20for%20a%20permanent%20middle%20management%20layer%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20else%20the%20old%20hierarchy%20did%2C%20the%20system%20coordinates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20an%20episode%20of%20Sequoia%20Capital's%20%26quot%3BLong%20Strange%20Trip%26quot%3B%20podcast%20published%20Thursday%2C%20Dorsey%20said%20that%20he%20aims%20to%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20layers%20between%20the%20company's%206%2C000%20employees%20and%20himself%20this%20year%20to%20two%20or%20three%2C%20down%20from%20about%20five.%20The%20%26quot%3Bmost%20ideal%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20would%20be%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-dorsey-all-6000-employees-reporting-ceo-middle-managers-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20layers%20at%20all%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20in%20the%20company%20reports%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Dorsey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20declined%20to%20comment%20and%20Block%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShifting%20to%20small%2C%20cross-functional%20teams%20can%20help%20companies%20innovate%20more%20quickly%20by%20bringing%20together%20employees%20with%20complementary%20skills%2C%20said%20Linda%20Hill%2C%20a%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20professor%20and%20cofounder%20of%20the%20AI-driven%20software%20startup%20InnovationForce.%20However%2C%20they%20also%20need%20what%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bbridgers%2C%26quot%3B%20human%20leaders%20who%20can%20help%20those%20teams%20collaborate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20rarely%20get%20innovation%20without%20diversity%20of%20thought%20and%20expertise%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20may%20be%20able%20to%20get%20by%20with%20fewer%20workers%20now%20that%20AI%20can%20automate%20many%20tasks%2C%20and%20some%2C%20including%20Block%2C%20have%20said%20as%20much%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblock-lay-off-4000-employees-read-jack-dorseys-memo-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejustify%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%20fully%20offloading%20managers'%20responsibilities%20to%20AI%20simply%20isn't%20practical%2C%20said%20Patty%20McCord%2C%20the%20former%20Netflix%20chief%20talent%20officer%20who%20helped%20rethink%20traditional%20management%20structures%20through%20its%20famous%20%26quot%3Bculture%20deck%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20slide%20presentation%20advocating%20fewer%20managers%20and%20more%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20is%20not%20going%20to%20take%20humans%20out%20of%20the%20equation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Instead%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20going%20to%20take%20some%20tasks%20out%2C%20just%20like%20factories%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ac6606c-abcd-4a6f-92f6-4435b8cfec7c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20dangers%20of%20micromanaging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnorthodox%20hierarchies%20can%20backfire.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-zappos-self-management-system-holacracy-works-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZappos'%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%20to%20eliminate%20hierarchy%20and%20empower%20workers%20ultimately%20unraveled%20in%20practice.%20The%20experiment%2C%20which%20ditched%20manager%20roles%20and%20job%20titles%20in%20favor%20of%20%26quot%3Bself-management%2C%26quot%3B%20notoriously%20created%20ambiguity%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20accountability%20among%20the%20online%20retailer's%20workforce.%20A%20few%20hundred%20employees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftony-hsieh-zappos-holacracy-management-experiment-2015-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsequently%20quit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20always%20will%20need%20clarity%20on%20decision%20rights%20and%20accountability%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kaufman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZappos'%20experiment%2C%20however%2C%20wasn't%20tied%20to%20a%20major%20technological%20shift%2C%20whereas%20Meta%20and%20Block%20are%20responding%20to%20today's%20highly%20advanced%20agentic%20and%20generative%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStraying%20from%20traditional%20workforce%20structures%20might%20not%20make%20sense%20for%20some%20companies.%20Makers%20of%20medical%20devices%2C%20for%20example%2C%20typically%20need%20rigid%20structures%20because%20the%20cost%20of%20human%20error%20is%20too%20high%2C%20said%20McCord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaking%20up%20hierarchies%2C%20however%2C%20can%20and%20has%20worked%20for%20others%2C%20like%20Netflix.%20And%20at%20this%20moment%2C%20traditional%20top-down%20control%20may%20be%20less%20effective%20for%20software%20companies%20like%20Meta%20and%20Block%20since%20AI's%20full%20potential%20remains%20unknown%2C%20said%20McCord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20last%20thing%20you%20want%20when%20you're%20innovating%20is%20micromanagement%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20antithesis%20of%20innovation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20especially%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20when%20dealing%20with%20a%20technology%20that's%20not%20yet%20fully%20understood%2C%20such%20as%20AI%2C%20McCord%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20really%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20people%20who%20are%20over-controlling.%20They%20could%20be%20wrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDriving%20organizational%20change%20of%20any%20kind%20requires%20more%20than%20just%20revamping%20job%20titles%20and%20descriptions%2C%20said%20Jo-Ellen%20Pozner%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Santa%20Clara%20University's%20Leavey%20School%20of%20Business%20who%20researches%20and%20teaches%20organizational%20function%20and%20malfunction.%20Companies%20also%20need%20to%20set%20new%20performance%20goals%20and%20new%20ways%20to%20measure%20and%20reward%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20about%20implementation%2C%26quot%3B%20Pozner%20said.%20Otherwise%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20are%20just%20going%20to%20do%20the%20same%20things%20that%20they've%20always%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-block-managers-player-coaches-org-leads-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775296081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.i